<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[464,712,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Cook, D. R. (1991) Water mites. Chapter 16. In: Thorp, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. Academic Press, San Diego, CA, pp. 523 - 592. [total page number 911 pp.]" type="book chapter" year="1991">Smith &amp; Cook (1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[727,784,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Cook, D. R. (1999) An assessment of global distribution patterns in water mites (Acari: Hydrachnida). In: Needham, G. R., Mitchell, R. D., Horn, D. J. &amp; Welbourn, W. C. (Eds.), Acarology IX. Vol. 2. Symposia. Ohio Biological Survey, Columbus, pp. 109 - 124." type="book" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[854,1070,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M., Cook, D. R. &amp; Smith, B. P. (2001) Water mites and other arachnids. Chapter 16. In: Thorpe, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. 2 nd Edition. Academic Press, Waltham, Massachusetts, pp. 551 - 659. [1056 pp.] http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / B 978 - 012690647 - 9 / 50017 - X" type="book chapter" year="2001">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[932,983,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">et al</emphasis>
. (2001
</bibRefCitation>
, 2010) treated this clade as the subfamily Foreliinae. Gerecke (
<number box="[531,590,512,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) proposed placing 
<taxonomicName box="[830,969,513,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,969,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1041,1213,513,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1041,1213,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Foreliinae, apparently unaware that 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[432,582,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" refString="Smith, I. M. (1976) A study of the systematics of the water mite family Pionidae (Prostigmata: Parasitengona). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 98, 1 - 249." type="journal article" year="1976">
Smith (
<number box="[515,573,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had already assigned them to Foreliini. Here we follow Gerecke (
<number box="[1339,1398,548,572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) in considering 
<taxonomicName box="[288,427,585,608]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[288,427,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[482,654,585,608]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[482,654,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate genera.
